description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:749-756

When parsing DATA_PAYLOAD_FIELD, the payload pointer and length are stored directly:
  case DATA_PAYLOAD_FIELD:
      if (wt != PB_WT_LEN ||
          pb_read_len_value(&cur, &payload, &payload_len) < 0) {
          return -EINVAL;
      }
      info->payload = payload;
      info->payload_len = payload_len;
      break;

For text message payloads, this data is later used with UTF-8 validation but the packet is passed to handle_text() which may assume NUL-termination.

Looking at text_packet_supported (line 977-997):
  if (packet->payload == NULL || packet->payload_len == 0U ||
      packet->payload_len > LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_TEXT_PAYLOAD_MAX ||
      !utf8_is_valid(packet->payload, packet->payload_len)) {

The payload is validated for UTF-8 but not NUL-terminated. If handle_text callback uses string functions like strlen() or printf(%s) directly on payload, it would read past the buffer.

SECURITY: Handlers must be careful to use payload_len, not assume NUL termination.
